Interface ConcernSubmissionObserver

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public interface ConcernSubmissionObserver
extends java.io.Serializable
    This interface is implemented by MainViewModel and used by NewConcernViewModel to inform the MainViewModel that a concern has been submitted. The newly submitted concern is then added to the list of concerns stored on the device.
    Invariants:
    none.
    History Properties:
    none.

      • concernSubmitted

        void concernSubmitted(@NonNull
                      android.content.Context context,
                      @NonNull
                      ConcernWrapper concern)
        Only by NewConcernViewModel to inform MainViewModel that a new concern has been submitted. The new concern is added to the list of concerns in MainViewModel.
        Parameters:
